# AGENTS.md -- <APP NAME> rulebook (Cursor / Codex / any coding agent)

## Tech stack -- installed reality (update in the SAME commit as any env change)

| Fact | Value |
|---|---|
| App interpreter | `<C:/path/to/envs/app311/python.exe>` -- the launcher's env, NEVER the base/default env or `which python` |
| Dash | `<pin>` (must equal pyproject `==` pin; the verify version gate checks) |
| Boot | `<python run.py>` -> `<http://127.0.0.1:8051>` |
| State dir | `<path>` -- env-overridable via `<APP_STATE_DIR>` |
| Test env note | `<e.g. pytest + playwright + pytest-playwright pinned in the app env; if pytest errors on boot, fixing the toolchain IS the task -- do not fall back to weaker checks>` |

## The one verify command

    powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/verify.ps1

Exit 0 = green, exit 1 = red. This EXACT command is what the git pre-commit
hook runs. There is no weaker "quick check": if any doc shows a different
smoke command, this one wins -- report the drift instead of running the other.

## Non-negotiables

1. **Ground truth before editing.** Reproduce the symptom in the browser
   (screenshot, console error, or network evidence) BEFORE changing code.
   Check the build stamp first: a stale server makes every edit invisible.
2. **Done = pasted green verify output.** Never claim "smoke test passed"
   without running the command above in THIS session and pasting its tail.
   Unit tests are not proof for front-end behavior bugs.
3. **One bug per session; one commit per verified change.** No bundled diffs
   (fix + docs + refactor in one commit = un-revertable blast radius).
   Commit only after verify is green -- the hook enforces this.
4. **State sandbox.** Tests and verify must point `<APP_STATE_DIR>` at a temp
   copy. Nothing may write the real state dir.
5. **Version truth.** Write code for the INSTALLED versions in the table
   above, not what a stale doc claims. If the table disagrees with
   `importlib.metadata`, fixing the table is part of the change.

## Escapes -- humans only

`git commit --no-verify` and `SKIP_VERIFY=1` bypass the pre-commit gate.
Agents must never use them. If verify cannot run (broken toolchain), STOP and
report the breakage; do not route around the gate.
